{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04258/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04258"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:58"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["An eye illuminated by a small, circular light."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04258","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04258"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/0fc3ff7f-85e4-40f6-a25a-d198966799f9","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:37:19.747Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The light hitting Reynolds’s eye as he watches Alma through the peephole recalls the shot of the house’s <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW252267300 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-00251.html\"><u>skylight</u></a>. The light at once embodies the illumination she brings to his life and links Reynolds to his residence.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:684.7913862718708,770.6325706594887,505.1951547779274,187.34858681022877"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/3f400abb-c4ba-48e1-b208-558db3953f44","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:37:32.396Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Sima Movaghati places this shot in a long tradition of films that depict their male protagonists’ “scopophilic compulsion,” including&nbsp; Robert Siodmak's <em>The Spiral Staircase</em> (1946), Michael Powell’s <em>Peeping Tom </em>(1960), Edward Dmytryk’s <em>Bluebeard </em>(1972), and Michael Powell’s <em>Duke Bluebeard’s Castle</em> (1963) (Movaghati, “Bluebeard Meets Ivy,” 724).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:98.19650067294745,89.7173620457605,381.1574697173621,275.2086137281292"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1/f91acc78-17af-48fb-92ad-96a7e9ba03db","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:37:44.596Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Beyond these cinephilic influences, however, PTA also drew from the life of Cristóbal Balenciaga for this detail: “There was that peephole in the curtain and Balenciaga always had his eye to it. He saw everything, everything [during showings]” (Blume, <em>The Master of Us All</em>, 113).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04258/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:713.2166890982503,362.34185733512794,616.3122476446838,352.73216689098257"}}}]}]}]}